@thorneliu Good idea. Maybe These virtual functions can be added to RetryPolicy with default implementation that the retry backoff feature is turned off.  In a manner of:

``` c++
class RetryPolicy {
public:
    virtual ~RetryPolicy();
    virtual bool DoRetry(const Controller* controller) const = 0;
    virtual int32_t GetBackoffTimeMs(const Controller* controller, int nretry,
                                     int64_t remaining_rpc_time_ms) const { return 0; }
    virtual bool CanRetryBackoffInPthread() const { return false; }
};
```

`FixedRetryBackoffPolicy` and `JitteredRetryBackoffPolicy` inherit `RpcRetryPolicy` which implements the default rpc retry policy.

